Functional requirements and Nonfunctional requirements:

Functional Requirements (FR):

Student Functional Requirements:

• FR1: The system shall allow students to log in to the schedule builder platform.
• FR2: The system shall allow students to browse available courses and their time
slots.
• FR3: The system shall allow students to build their schedule step-by-step using the
Builder interface.
• FR4: The system shall allow students to check for time conflicts between selected
courses.
• FR5: The system shall allow students to view real-time capacity and seat availability
for each section.
• FR6: The system shall allow students to confirm and save their finalized built
schedule.
• FR7: The system shall allow students to view their previous academic schedules.

Instructor Functional Requirements:

• FR8: The system shall allow instructors to view a dashboard showing their assigned
sections.
• FR9: The system shall allow instructors to view the list of registered students in
their classes.
• FR10: The system shall allow instructors to monitor laboratory capacity and
equipment constraints.
• FR11: The system shall allow instructors to send announcements to students in
their specific sections.
• FR12: The system shall allow instructors to view student attendance and
engagement reports.
