Admin Functional Requirements:

• FR14: The system shall allow the admin to view an administrative dashboard for
system monitoring
• FR15: The system shall allow the admin to create, update, and delete course data
and time slots.
• FR16: The system shall allow the admin to add, edit, and remove student and
instructor accounts.
• FR17: The system shall allow the admin to set maximum capacity constraints for all
sections.
• FR18: The system shall allow the admin to view system-wide enrollment and
capacity reports.
• FR19: The system shall allow the admin to manage registration periods and system
access dates.
• FR20: The system shall allow the admin to update institutional settings and
department information

Guest Functional Requirements:

• FR21: The system shall allow guests to browse the public course catalog without
logging in.
• FR22: The system shall allow guests to view general university information and
registration guides.
• FR23: The system shall allow guests to register for a new student account

Manager Functional Requirements:

• FR24: The system shall allow the manager to view a dashboard with registration
and demand insights.
• FR25: The system shall allow the manager to view overall system performance and
resource reports.
• FR26: The system shall allow the manager to view capacity statistics to assist in
decision-making.

Accountant Functional Requirements:

• FR27: The system shall allow the accountant to view a financial dashboard related
to registration fees.
• FR28: The system shall allow the accountant to manage, verify, and track student
payment statuses.
