Non-Functional Requirements (NFR):

• NFR1: The system shall protect student and user data using high-level encryption.
• NFR2: The system shall apply role-based access control for all types of users.
• NFR3: The system shall ensure data integrity for all schedule and capacity
information.
• NFR4: Dashboards shall load within 3 seconds under normal and peak usage.
• NFR5: Conflict detection and capacity checks shall respond efficiently without
delays.
• NFR6: Capacity and enrollment reports shall be generated within 5 seconds.
• NFR7: The system shall provide a simple and intuitive user interface for all roles.
• NFR8: The system shall be available 24/7 with minimal scheduled maintenance.
• NFR9: The system shall support at least 10,000 concurrent users during
registration.
• NFR10: The system shall be compatible with all major web browsers (Chrome,
Edge, Safari).
• NFR11: The system shall automatically log users out after a period of inactivity for
security.
• NFR12: All system activities and registration changes shall be logged for auditing
purposes.
• NFR13: Regular database backups shall be performed to prevent any loss of
schedule data
